OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FGiven some MPs have been referring to
OL,7,Fthe King's brother today as a "rude,
OL,8,Farrogant and entitled man", where are
OL,9,Fwe on the convention that members of
OL,10,Fparliament cannot criticise the Royal
OL,11,FFamily?
OL,13,FThe House of Commons library assures
OL,14,Fus that MPs are not prevented from
OL,15,Fcriticising the King and members of
OL,16,Fhis family.
OL,18,FBut both MPs and Lords are required to
OL,19,Fstick to certain rules if they do wish
OL,20,Fto do so.
OL,26,@oD@_OUpD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FConfusion comes from the Commons rule
OL,7,Fbook, called Erskine May, which is the
OL,8,F'bible' of regulations and formalities
OL,9,Fin both Houses of Parliament.
OL,11,FIt tells members that "reflections
OL,12,Fmust not be cast in debate upon the
OL,13,Fconduct of the sovereign, the heir to
OL,14,Fthe throne or other members of the
OL,15,FRoyal Family".
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,26,@sD@WOUwD@MO]
