PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FNor can MPs or Lords use the King's -
OL,7,For previously Queen Elizabeth's ` name
OL,8,Fin order to influence the debate, such
OL,9,Fas saying "it would make the King very
OL,10,Fhappy" if we were to do this or that.
OL,12,FAccording to the Speaker's Office,
OL,13,Fthose rules exist to keep parliament
OL,14,Findependent of the monarch (which
OL,15,Fdates back to the English Civil War
OL,16,Fand the execution of King Charles I)
OL,17,Fand to keep the monarch above politics
OL,18,Fand avoid him or her being dragged
OL,19,Finto political issues of the day.
OL,26,@qD@KOUrD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
