PN,31306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FInterestingly, the rules which apply
OL,7,Fto the Royal Family also apply to
OL,8,Fthose who hold the office of Lord
OL,9,FChancellor, members of either House of
OL,10,FParliament, senior judges and the
OL,11,Fgovernor-generals of a realm country
OL,12,F(they are the sovereign's
OL,13,Frepresentatives in countries, like
OL,14,FCanada, Australia, New Zealand,
OL,15,FJamaica, Belize, where the British
OL,16,Fmonarch remains the head of state).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FThat said, Tuesday's debate was
OL,7,Funaffected by these constraints, given
OL,8,Fthat Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor is no
OL,9,Flonger a working member of the Royal
OL,10,FFamily and has lost his prince title
OL,11,Fand his dukedom.
OL,13,FHe does remain eighth in the line of
OL,14,Fsuccession, and also a counsellor of
OL,15,Fstate (a senior royal who can stand in
OL,16,Ffor the King), but the UK government
OL,17,Fhas indicated it will find time for
OL,18,Flegislation to remove Andrew from this
OL,19,Fline.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772010305
OL,3,CCan MPs criticise the Royal Family in
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons?
OL,6,FAustralia and New Zealand are two
OL,7,Frealms that have already said they
OL,8,Fwill support this move ` as any change
OL,9,Fto the line of succession requires
OL,10,Fapproval in the UK and the other 14
OL,11,Frealms where King Charles is head of
OL,12,Fstate.
OL,14,FGiven MPs had the chance to give their
OL,15,Freflections "upon the conduct" of
OL,16,FAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor today, they
OL,17,Fdidn't hold back.
OL,19,F"A stain on our country," said Liberal
OL,20,FDemocrat leader Sir Ed Davey.
OL,26,@wD@MOUwD@^O]{D@AOU{D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
